    <refentrytitle>AUTOINSTALLSCRIPT.CONF</refentrytitle>

    &dhsection;
  </refmeta>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>autoinstallscript.conf</refname>

    <refpurpose>Obsolete file used to specify client disk configuration (partitions, filesystems, bootloader(s).</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsect1>
  <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
  <para>
    The <filename>autoinstallscript.conf</filename> is now obsolete. Its historical location was /var/lib/systemimager/images/&lt;imagename&gt;/etc/systemimager/autoinstallscript.conf. It was used by si_mkautoinstallscript to create client disk(s) initialisation commands in the client dedicated autoinstall script. This file is generated by si_prepareclient on golden client and saved in /etc/systemimager/autoinstallscript.conf so it is later transfered by si_getimage in the image server.
  </para>

  <para>
    The <filename>autoinstallscript.conf</filename> is now stored in /var/lib/systemimager/scripts/disks-layouts/ on the image server and has a new bootloader section. It is directly parsed and used by the imager. Man <filename>systemimager.disks-layout(7)</filename> for more informations.
  </para>

  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
  <title>MIGRATION TO NEW DISKS-LAYOUT</title>

  <para>
    Simply move the /var/lib/systemimager/images/&lt;imagename&gt;/etc/systemimager/autoinstallscript.conf to /var/lib/systemimager/scripts/disks-layouts/&lt;imagename&gt;.xml (or any suitable name ending with xml extension) and add a mandatory bootloader section. More informations may be found in <filename>systemimager.disks-layout(7)</filename> manual.
  </para>

  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>EXAMPLES</title>

  <para>
     A simple disk layout for a single disk with an mdos (legacy) partition table: <filename>/usr/share/doc/systemimager-doc*/examples/disk-layout-simple.xml</filename>
  </para>

  <para>
     A more complex disk layout with extended and logicals partitions using msdos (legacy) partition table: <filename>/usr/share/doc/systemimager-doc*/examples/disk-layout-complex.xml</filename>
  </para>

  <para>
     An even more complex setup using two disks that forms a soft raid one on wich we configure lvm and then partions: <filename>/usr/share/doc/systemimager-doc*/examples/disk-layout-lvm_over_raid.xml</filename>
  </para>

  <para>
     A layout designed for an EFI system. Note: when choosing EFI, the image deployed must already include the linux EFI packages otherwise the imager will stop at bootloader install (on RHEL-7, it's the grub2-efi-x64 package that must be present in image): <filename>/usr/share/doc/systemimager-doc*/examples/disk-layout-EFI.xml</filename>
  </para>

  </refsect1>

